   "source": [
    "##Continuum Opacity Source Reader:\n",
    "\n",
    "##Version: Prototype 0.01\n",
    "\n",
    "##Author: Sanhik Nandi\n",
    "\n",
    "##Date: 22-3-24\n",
    "\n",
    "Welcome to the Continuum Opacity Source Reader. This Notebook is a step by step walkthrough of how we can use this module to read scientific literature data from\n",
    ".gz files and returns a Pandas DataFrame that contains the required data to be fed into the Carsus engine or be directly used."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "abfaa96ea1e18c3f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The Continuum Opacity Source Reader is a file meant to read data from Scientific literature in the form of .gzip files. The file has to be imported from the Continuum Opacity source Reader Module. The module contains a single class : OpacityReader which in turn contains 2 functions :\n",
    "1. ##__init__(file_path(required, takes a string argument), masking_value(optional, default = None, takes integer value), skip_rows(optional, default = 0, takes integer value)##: This is the constructor file of the program and is used to intialise) the class variables that the program shall later use.\n",
    "2. ##read(: This is the function that actually reads the data from the file and returns a Pandas Dataframe of the data collected from the file. The file currently only reads from .gz files.|"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b2f6bc41345e6c1a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now that we are introduced to the project as well as it's methods, let us try to use the Continuum Opacity Source Reader to read fron a source file, that will be s92.201.gz file that is stored in the Datasets folder.\n",
    "\n",
    "First we shall import the Continuum Opacity Source Reader."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "id": "4565165a2dd0e723",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2026-03-24T12:24:03.848027Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2026-03-24T12:24:03.847403Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2026-03-24T12:24:04.620137Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2026-03-24T12:24:04.619677Z"
    },
    "ExecuteTime": {
