     "start_time": "2026-03-24T13:39:21.439402656Z"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "from tardis.io.continuum_reader.s92_reader import OpacityReader"
   ],
   "outputs": [],
   "execution_count": 1
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9a7e17809e58666a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now that we have the module imported, let us try to use it to read the s92.201.gz fiole. For that we shall first get the location of the required file and shall use the OS module for that."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "id": "a9c17ef36ea4af79",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2026-03-24T12:24:04.621969Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2026-03-24T12:24:04.621749Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2026-03-24T12:24:04.624473Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2026-03-24T12:24:04.624123Z"
    },
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2026-03-24T13:39:21.791441300Z",
     "start_time": "2026-03-24T13:39:21.773228871Z"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "\n",
    "file_path = os.path.join(\"..\",\"dataset\",\"s92.201.gz\")\n",
    "\n",
    "#Let's print to see if it's working:\n",
    "print(f\"The file Path is {file_path}\")"
   ],
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "The file Path is ../dataset/s92.201.gz\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "execution_count": 2
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8c8877e9a92a971",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now that we have the daqtaset path loaded, let us try to read data from it using the Continuum Opacity Source Reader. We shall the program by creating the object with the file_path with the file_path we found using os.path.join() method and shall use the masking_value = 20 and skip_rows = 120"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "id": "c2a54362e42828d8",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2026-03-24T12:24:04.625794Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2026-03-24T12:24:04.625648Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2026-03-24T12:24:04.647497Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2026-03-24T12:24:04.647128Z"
    },
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2026-03-24T13:39:21.846074603Z",
     "start_time": "2026-03-24T13:39:21.795841618Z"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "reader_new = OpacityReader(file_path,masking_value=120, skip_rows=20)\n",
    "#Next we shall call the read function to read from the file_path and it will return a dataset to us containing the data that we needed.\n",
    "df = reader_new.read()\n",
    "#let us print the dataset next.\n",
    "df.head()"
   ],
